If we use the substitution

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle u=2y+y^2
\end{align*} then

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle du=(2+2y)\,dy =2(1+y)\,dy
\end{align*} and

\begin{align*}
\int_0^1 (y+1)\sqrt{2y+y^2}\,  dy &= \frac12 \int_0^3 \sqrt{u}\, du\\
&= \frac12 \left[\frac23 u^{3/2}\right]_0^3\\
&= \frac13 3^{3/2} \\
&= \sqrt3.
\end{align*}
